# Cybersecurity and Global Impacts Unit Overview
 
#### While the Cybersecurity and Global Impacts Unit is part of the **Computer Science and AI Foundations** course, they can also serve as a standalone unit for 9-12 students that can be integrated seamlessly into existing curriculum, including computer science, math, or science, offering teachers the flexibility to introduce it according to their schedule and educational needs.

#### This unit consists of 10 lessons, takes about three weeks to complete, and does not have Python programming.

<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; background: #f7f8fa; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto;">

  <div>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 0; font-weight: bold;">Students will:</h4>
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14pt">
      <li>Learn how <strong>computing innovations</strong> have impacted our world in beneficial and harmful ways.</li>
      <li>Learn how <strong>data</strong> can pose a threat to our privacy and security and the ways that encryption and other techniques are used to protect it.</li>
      <li>Participate in a <strong>"school of the future"</strong> conference in which you and a team make a proposal for how best to improve school life with computing innovations.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
